        "orario": "14:20",
        "timestamp": 1773408020,
        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. REPLAY: Macron, Zelensky hold press conference in Paris Issued on: 13/03/2026 - 14:20 The war ​in the Middle ​East will not give Russia respite in its own ​conflict ‌with ⁠Ukraine, French President Emmanuel Macron said ‌on Friday during a ⁠visit by Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskiy in ​Paris. Macron added that ‌it was strange to see Russia calling ‌for a ceasefire in the ​Middle East when it obstinately refuses to accept one with ​Ukraine. Macron said France's ​support for ​Ukraine would remain resolute and he ​was determined to continue military support for Ukraine. War in Ukraine: Zelensky meets Macron for talks on Russia 13/03/2026 REPLAY: US Defense Secretary holds press conference on Iran war 13/03/2026 Strait of Hormuz: Iran leverages control of a critical chokepoint in the global oil trade 13/03/2026 Middle East French officer killed in drone attack in Iraq 13/03/2026 In Ukraine, war forces schools below ground to keep classes going 13/03/2026 War in the Middle East: New wave of attacks on Gulf states 13/03/2026 French soldier killed in attack in Iraqi Kurdistan 13/03/2026 In first public comments, Iran’s supreme leader pledges to keep fighting 13/03/2026 Middle East: Millions forced from their homes since the start of the war 13/03/2026"
